cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.PF, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a framework for modeling and analyzing linear communication networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the movement of data-packets along a one-dimensional chain of buffers, which can be seen as a type of information flow in a network. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper provides closed-form expressions for network metrics such as throughput and end-to-end delay, which are important concepts in information theory. 
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the optimal parameter values for minimizing end-to-end delay in a multihop linear network, which is a performance-related issue. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The concept of decentralized backpressure flow control in the RFM can be seen as a type of control system, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
